Well, ive had a busy day.

I tried for my permit again, and failed by one point. I expected to be upset if I failed again, but I actually think Im glad that I failed. I learned so much more about driving this time around, and I think that Ill feel safer driving once I have my permit.

Philip went to New York today. I never really let him know until now, but hes so important in my life. I dont know if its like that with all the little brothers I hang out with whose silblings have gone off past high school. Philip's really awesome, and if youre reading this, I just wanted you to know that you have my support in everything you do.

I finally got on the list to get out of PE for a sport. Ive been waiting for a week now. ^^ Swimming should be a blast.

I think im going to make a personal form in Taekwondo. Yeah.

Well, Ill come back later.

Everyone needs to CHILL OUT!

I swear, everyone in my life is FREAKING OUT! I think the only non-angsty-freakedout person I know is Wilson, and everyone else is way too high strung.

Everyone's like "Oh no! I need somebody to love!" or "Oh my god! Everybody is out to get me!" or "I dont have time for this!" or "I cant afford to have to do that!"...

Chill out.

Byron - You make great grades, chill. Just because you have a bad day, bleh.
Neale - Stop stealing my pens and get some sleep. SLEEP! X BALLISTA! SLEEP!
Hunter - Well, I guess youre not so bad, but just be cool. Be cool.
Brittany - Take a chill pill, relax. We (including me) need to stop taking things seriously and just let the clouds pass by.
Bret - You stopped cursing, and thats good. Now, stop talking about "Sarah this", "Sarah that".
Catmur - Stop being so secretive. Do you want to go out with Angela or not?
Me - Go to Taekwondo.

For those of you who know me, Im.. ah fuck, lemme start over.

Oh screw it. 
This isn't my first time here, I used to be Tantan12. I decided it was time for a new name.
Im the same person I was before, but a little over half a year has passed, and little things have changed me a bit. Im a little more agnsty... and wow... I just misspelled angsty.

It seems like my life is like... well... a piece of hand-woven cloth. Its been beautiful for a very long time, but it seems like something is pulling at the seam. Little by little the thread is being pulled around the sides. I dont know whats going to happen, but im not just going to let everything happen and land wherever.

I will fly above this chaos I call my life on wings of glory.
